As we can see from the previous test, the normal distribution model can not be used. We can confirm this data by using the following texts

library(nortest)

3.2 Fitting a Weibull distribution

library(fitdistrplus)
weibullfit <- fitdist(loud, "weibull")
weibullfit
## Fitting of the distribution ' weibull ' by maximum likelihood 
## Parameters:
##        estimate Std. Error
## shape  1.649592 0.08687057
## scale 10.771187 0.53790263
Partition <- hist(loud, plot=FALSE)
Partition
## $breaks
##  [1]  0  5 10 15 20 25 30 35 40 45
## 
## $counts
## [1]  21 104  23   6   5   4   1   2   1
## 
## $density
## [1] 0.025149701 0.124550898 0.027544910 0.007185629 0.005988024 0.004790419
## [7] 0.001197605 0.002395210 0.001197605
## 
## $mids
## [1]  2.5  7.5 12.5 17.5 22.5 27.5 32.5 37.5 42.5
## 
## $xname
## [1] "loud"
## 
## $equidist
## [1] TRUE
## 
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "histogram"
CummulativeProbabilities = pweibull(c(Partition$breaks[-10], Inf), weibullfit$estimate[1], weibullfit$estimate[2])
Probabilities = diff(CummulativeProbabilities)
Expected = length(loud)*Probabilities 
chisq.test(Partition$counts, p = Probabilities)
## Warning in chisq.test(Partition$counts, p = Probabilities): Chi-squared
## approximation may be incorrect
## 
##  Chi-squared test for given probabilities
## 
## data:  Partition$counts
## X-squared = 128.67, df = 8, p-value < 2.2e-16
pchisq(128.67, 6, lower.tail = FALSE)
## [1] 2.449221e-25
plot(weibullfit)

3.4 Fitting a Normal distribution to a transformation of the dataset

#4. Aplication od the goodness-of-fit ### Computing using Weibull

cat("Our data vs a normal distribution ")
## Our data vs a normal distribution
pnorm(60, mean=125.8656, sd=27.0737, lower.tail=FALSE)
## [1] 0.9925092
cat("Our data vs a weibull distribution ")
## Our data vs a weibull distribution
pweibull(60, shape=1.649592, scale=10.771187, lower.tail=FALSE)
## [1] 4.146192e-08

Computation using the Normal model applied to the square- root of the variable

pnorm(sqrt(60), mean = 2.96006217, sd =  0.87631623 , lower.tail = FALSE)
## [1] 2.362107e-08
plot(ecdf(loud))
lines(0:130, pweibull(0:130, shape = 1.649592, scale = 10.771187), col="red") 
lines(0:130, pnorm(sqrt(0:130), mean = 125.8656, sd = 27.0737), col="blue")
